article.headline: Long Beach St 91, UC Riverside 75
article.story: RIVERSIDE, Calif. (AP) -- Sterling Byrd had 23 points as Long Beach State took a 91-75 victory over UC Riverside to close out its regular season Saturday. The 49ers (22-7, 12-2 Big West) finished in first place in the conference. The Highlanders (7-23, 1-13) ended in eighth place. The 49ers broke open the contest midway through the second half, pushing their advantage to 70-56 at 9:36 after a tip-in by Louis Darby. UC Riverside pulled to within 73-65 with 6:31 left but the 49ers went on a 16-3 run to take command, 89-68. The 49ers knocked down 11 3-pointers on 23 attempts and out-rebounded the Highlanders 41-to-31. Aaron Nixon had 18 points, Kevin Houston 15 and Kejuan Johnson added 16 points and eight rebounds for Long Beach. Larry Cunningham led with 18 points while Chris Johnson added 15 and Henrik Thomsen 14.
